<paragraph blockId="8.[166,1225,1439,1850]" pageId="8" pageNumber="33">
D i a g n o s i s. This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Korneyev" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="Hendel" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[695,841,1439,1466]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Afropyrgota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marshalli">
<emphasis box="[695,841,1439,1466]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="33">A. marshalli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having two pairs of scutellar setae, and frontal vitta yellow, similar shape and length of oviscape, differing from it by having entirely reddish yellow setulose body, including pleura, abdomen and legs (pleura, abdomen and legs black setulose in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Korneyev" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="Hendel" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[593,737,1535,1562]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Afropyrgota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marshalli">
<emphasis box="[593,737,1535,1562]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="33">A. marshalli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and mid femur with cuneiform femoral organ narrower than femur (entirely lacking in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Korneyev" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="Hendel" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[724,867,1567,1594]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Afropyrgota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marshalli">
<emphasis box="[724,867,1567,1594]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="33">A. marshalli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[166,1225,1439,1850]" lastBlockId="9.[174,1233,175,490]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="34" pageId="8" pageNumber="33">
D e s c r i p t i o n. Head (
<figureCitation box="[502,564,1599,1626]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[174,207,1710,1732]" captionTargetBox="[206,1193,536,1669]" captionTargetId="figure-147@9.[206,1194,536,1678]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig.6. Afropyrgota ota sp. n., ♀: 1 — holotype, lateral view; 2–4 — head (2 —left, 3 — anterior, 4 — dorsal view); 5 — wing; 6 — mid leg, anterior; 7 — prosternum, anteroventral; 8 — paratype abdomen, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404041" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404041/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="33">fig. 6</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis box="[577,620,1599,1625]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="33">
<figureCitation box="[577,593,1599,1625]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[166,199,604,626]" captionTargetBox="[202,1177,169,589]" captionTargetId="figure-456@4.[195,1196,158,590]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. Afropyrgota copelandi sp. n., ♀: 1 — sternite 6 and oviscape, ventrolateral view; 2 — same, lateroventral and dorsomedial lobes, left; 3 — aculeus; 4 — vagina and ventral receptacle; 5 — spermatheca. dl — dorsal lobe; lvl — lateroventral lobe; mva — medioventral desclerotized area; st6 — sternite 6; vr — ventral receptacle." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404031" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404031/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="33">2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[606,620,1599,1625]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[174,207,1677,1699]" captionTargetBox="[209,1194,805,1654]" captionTargetId="figure-224@5.[205,1202,802,1660]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig.3. Afropyrgota mambilla sp. n., ♀: 1 — holotype, lateral view; 2– 4 — head (2 — left, 3 — anterior, 4 — dorsal view); 5 — mesonotum, dorsal view; 6 — fore leg, posterior; 7 — mid leg, anterior; 8 — oviscape, lateroventral; 9 — same, apex, ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404033" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404033/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="33">3</figureCitation>
</emphasis>
) yellow, frontal vitta yellow, c. 1.1 times as long as wide in posterior half; parafacial 1.73 times as wide as flagellomere 1; eye 2 times as high as wide, 1.3 times as wide as parafacial and 2.6 times as high as gena. Face concave, with low, but conspicuous medial carina, in 
<typeStatus box="[584,687,1695,1722]" pageId="8" pageNumber="33">holotype</typeStatus>
uniformly yellow, in 
<typeStatus box="[950,1052,1695,1722]" pageId="8" pageNumber="33">paratype</typeStatus>
with 2 brown spots ventrally. Gena with dark brown vertical patch over subocular sclerite. Occiput entirely yellow. First flagellomere entirely orange yellow, 2.7–2.8 times as long as wide, 1.72 times as long as pedicel and 3 times as long as scape. Arista entirely reddish yellow, 2-segmented. Scape 2 times as long as wide. Palp yellow, cylindric, 4–4.5 times as long as wide, and c. 0.8 times as long as first flagellomere. Labellum very large, but shorter than eye height. Lateral vertical setae (vte) distinctive, 0.5–0.6 times as long as medial vertical seta; the latter (vti) as long as pedicel and 1.6–1.8 times as long as postocellar, ocellar and orbital setae and 2.5 times as long as mesofrontal setulae (above lunule).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[174,1233,175,490]" pageId="9" pageNumber="34">
Thorax yellow to orange yellow, without dark pattern. Postpronotal lobe with 8– 10 setulae and one long seta; proepisternum with 7–9 setae; prosternum saddle-like (
<figureCitation box="[1166,1228,335,362]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[174,207,1710,1732]" captionTargetBox="[206,1193,536,1669]" captionTargetId="figure-147@9.[206,1194,536,1678]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig.6. Afropyrgota ota sp. n., ♀: 1 — holotype, lateral view; 2–4 — head (2 —left, 3 — anterior, 4 — dorsal view); 5 — wing; 6 — mid leg, anterior; 7 — prosternum, anteroventral; 8 — paratype abdomen, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404041" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404041/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="34">fig. 6</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[174,188,368,394]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[173,206,1383,1405]" captionTargetBox="[207,1168,189,1353]" captionTargetId="figure-116@11.[205,1179,174,1361]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 7. Afropyrgota uzungwa sp. n., ♀: 1 — holotype, lateral view; 2, 3 — head (2 — left, 3 — anterior); 4 — mesonotum dorsal; 5 — wing; 6 — fore leg, posterior; 7 — mid leg, anterior; 8 — hind leg, anterior and abdomen, ventrolateral. Scale bar 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404204" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404204/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis box="[174,188,368,394]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="34">7</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). Scutum 1.1–1.2 times as long as wide, subshining yellow with orange areas at place of attachment of muscles, sparsely yellow setulose, with white microtrichia not obscuring underlying cuticle; orange to brown setose, 2 notopleural, 1 supra-alar, 1 intra-alar, 1 postalar, 1–2 postsutural dorsocentral, and 0 acrostichal setae. Scutellum yellow, inconspicuously
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404041" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6404041" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404041/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="34" startId="9.[174,207,1710,1732]" targetBox="[206,1193,536,1669]" targetPageId="9">
