<paragraph blockId="10.[170,1229,175,906]" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">
whitish microtrichose, with one pair of apical setae 1.5 times as long as scutellum, but without setulae. Anepisternum yellow, in 
<typeStatus box="[605,707,207,234]" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">holotype</typeStatus>
uniformly yellow, in 
<typeStatus box="[958,1059,207,234]" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">paratype</typeStatus>
with dark yellow or brownish anterior part; posterior part with 2–4 long setae and 10–12 irregular long setae; anepimeron with 2–3 long setae and 3–6 irregular long setae; katepisternum with 1– 3 long setae and 9–15 thinner and slightly shorter setulae posterodorsally. Katatergite, anatergite and mediotergite brownish yellow, subshining, very sparsely whitish microtrichose.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[170,1229,175,906]" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">
Wing (
<figureCitation box="[302,360,367,394]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[174,207,1710,1732]" captionTargetBox="[206,1193,536,1669]" captionTargetId="figure-147@9.[206,1194,536,1678]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig.6. Afropyrgota ota sp. n., ♀: 1 — holotype, lateral view; 2–4 — head (2 —left, 3 — anterior, 4 — dorsal view); 5 — wing; 6 — mid leg, anterior; 7 — prosternum, anteroventral; 8 — paratype abdomen, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404041" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404041/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">fig. 6</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[371,385,368,394]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[173,206,1732,1754]" captionTargetBox="[232,1182,721,1694]" captionTargetId="figure-268@7.[225,1182,709,1696]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 5. Afropyrgota marshalli, holotype Ơ: 1 — lateral view; 2 — labels, 3 — wing; 4 — mesonotum, dorsal view; 5 — epandrium, right view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404039" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404039/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis box="[371,385,368,394]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">5</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
) pale yellowish along anterior margin and veins, covered with greyish microtrichia, with lighter areas between bm-cu and r-m and r-m and dm-cu; cell bm and alula mostly glossy, translucent, devoid of microtrichia. Vein R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[819,845,449,465]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">4+5</subScript>
bare. Wing length 10.5–14.0 mm. Lower calypter very narrow, without cilia; upper calypter with yellow fringe basally and 3– 4 yellow cilia half 0.4 times as long as calypter width. Halter creamy white, with brownish knob.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[170,1229,175,906]" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">
Legs entirely yellow, brown setulose and brownish yellow setose. Coxae moderately long and sparsely setose and setulose, unmodified. Fore femur moderately narrow, long setose on posterior surface. Mid femur (
<figureCitation box="[650,713,591,618]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[174,207,1710,1732]" captionTargetBox="[206,1193,536,1669]" captionTargetId="figure-147@9.[206,1194,536,1678]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig.6. Afropyrgota ota sp. n., ♀: 1 — holotype, lateral view; 2–4 — head (2 —left, 3 — anterior, 4 — dorsal view); 5 — wing; 6 — mid leg, anterior; 7 — prosternum, anteroventral; 8 — paratype abdomen, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404041" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404041/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">fig. 6</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[727,741,592,618]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[173,206,1383,1405]" captionTargetBox="[207,1168,189,1353]" captionTargetId="figure-116@11.[205,1179,174,1361]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 7. Afropyrgota uzungwa sp. n., ♀: 1 — holotype, lateral view; 2, 3 — head (2 — left, 3 — anterior); 4 — mesonotum dorsal; 5 — wing; 6 — fore leg, posterior; 7 — mid leg, anterior; 8 — hind leg, anterior and abdomen, ventrolateral. Scale bar 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404204" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404204/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis box="[727,741,592,618]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">7</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
) on anterior surface setose in basal onequarter and with cuneiform femoral organ narrower than its width and much shorter than its half. Hind femur narrow, short setulose without long setae (except basiventral seta).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[170,1229,175,906]" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">
Abdomen (
<figureCitation box="[355,416,687,714]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[174,207,1710,1732]" captionTargetBox="[206,1193,536,1669]" captionTargetId="figure-147@9.[206,1194,536,1678]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig.6. Afropyrgota ota sp. n., ♀: 1 — holotype, lateral view; 2–4 — head (2 —left, 3 — anterior, 4 — dorsal view); 5 — wing; 6 — mid leg, anterior; 7 — prosternum, anteroventral; 8 — paratype abdomen, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404041" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404041/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">fig. 6</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[427,441,687,713]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="12.[170,202,937,959]" captionTargetBox="[281,1146,182,923]" captionTargetId="figure-16@12.[227,1150,174,938]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Fig. 8. Afropyrgota uzungwa sp. n., paratype ♀: 1 — abdomen left view; 2 — oviscape (macerated) ventral; 3 — same, ventrolateral; 4 — same, apex, enlarged, ventrally; 5 — aculeus; 6 — spermatheca. Abbreviations as on fig 2." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404206" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404206/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis box="[427,441,687,713]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">8</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
) narrow, cylindrical, almost twice as long as thorax, with syntergite 1+2 elongate, 1.2 times as long as tergites 3–6 combined. Sternites as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Korneyev" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="Hendel" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[1008,1151,719,746]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Afropyrgota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marshalli">
<emphasis box="[1008,1151,719,746]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">A. marshalli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Oviscape as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Korneyev" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="Hendel" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[295,440,751,778]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Afropyrgota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marshalli">
<emphasis box="[295,440,751,778]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">A. marshalli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, entirely orange, short and sparsely black setulose, uncompressed, almost as high as wide and as long as tergites 3–6 combined, with apex short and slightly bent ventrally, bearing very short dorsomedial and two lateroventral lobes, but neither hooks, nor long setulae. Eversible membrane and aculeus not dissected.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[170,1229,175,906]" box="[223,409,879,906]" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">Male unknown.</paragraph>
